✅ KEEP (Core RHEL 9 CIS controls)

These are enforceable, high-value, and align with current CIS RHEL 9 Level 1 guidance.

Access control & authentication

check_user_expiry (5.4.1.1) – Ensures password expiry is configured.

check_users_MIN_DAYS (5.4.1.2) – Enforces minimum days between password changes.

passwd_auth_faillock (5.3.2.2) – Locks account after failed logins.

system_auth_faillock (5.3.2.2) – Same for system-auth (both needed).

system_auth_pwhistory (5.3.2.4) – Ensures password history is enforced.

passwd_auth_pwhistory (5.3.2.4) – Same for password-auth.

pam_unix_nullok_system-auth (5.3.3.4.1) – Disallow null passwords.

pam_unix_nullok_password-auth (5.3.3.4.1) – Same for password-auth.

passwd_auth_pam_unix (5.3.2.5) and system_auth_pam_unix (5.3.2.5) – Ensure pam_unix is active.

passwd_auth_authselect_modules & system_auth_authselect_modules (5.3.2.1) – Verify authselect profile integrity.

sugroup_etc_group (5.2.7) – Restricts su command to authorized users.

System auditing

auditd_priv_cmds_cnf (6.3.3.6) – Captures privileged command use (important for SOX/PCI compliance).

auditd_chacl_live (6.3.3.17) – Tracks ACL modifications.

Network security

firewalld_loopback_manual (4.2.2) – Ensures loopback traffic protection (manual verify).

firewall_drop_unncessary_ports_manual (4.2.1) – Required to meet “restrict open ports.”

Package verification

repo_gpgcheck_global (1.2.1.3) – Must be true.

repo_gpgcheck_repo (1.2.1.3) – Redundant but safe to keep (applies at repo level).

Login banners

etc_issue_config (1.7.2) – Banner configuration.

1.7.5 – Permissions on /etc/issue.

System hardening

autofs_masked (2.1.1) – Disables unneeded automounting.

wireless_disabled (3.1.2) – Disable unused wireless interfaces.

cron_allow_users (2.4.1.8) – Restrict cron.

at_allow_users (2.4.2.1) – Restrict at.

passwd_chg_past (5.4.1.6) – Ensures users’ passwords are not older than their last change date (sanity check).

Logging

systemd-journal-upload.service (6.2.2.1.3) – Ensures remote journaling is active.

journald_remote_config (6.2.2.1.2) – Validates secure upload config.
